# cp .env.example .env to configure the web dev server.
#
# The dashboard uses per-user session auth (a login screen + an HTTP-only
# session cookie), so there is no build-time API token to set here anymore —
# VITE_DASHBOARD_TOKEN has been retired.

# Base URL for the dashboard API. Leave unset for a same-origin deploy (the
# recommended setup); set it only when the SPA is served from a different
# origin than the API during development. A cross-origin API must allow this
# origin via CORS_ORIGIN in the repo-root .env — the default there already
# permits the Vite dev server (http://localhost:5173), so `npm run dev` works
# unchanged; only set CORS_ORIGIN if you serve the SPA from some other origin.
# VITE_API_URL=
